Installation:

    git clone git://github.com/dmayle/dm-dotfiles.git ~/.dm-dotfiles

Create symlinks:

    ln -s .dm-dotfiles/vim ~/.vim
    ln -s .dm-dotfiles/bash/bashrc ~/.bashrc
    ln -s .dm-dotfiles/bash/bash_profile ~/.bashrc
    ln -s .dm-dotfiles/inputrc ~/.inputrc
    ln -s .vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Switch to the `~/.dm-dotfiles` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.dm-dotfiles
    git submodule update --init

Add this to your crontab to auto-update everyday at 3am.
    0 3 * * * (cd ~/.dm-dotfiles && (git pull https://github.com/dmayle/dm-dotfiles; git submodule update --init)) &>/dev/null

Software required:
    Mac:
        MacVim (in order to get a vim compiled with python and ruby support)
        Exuberant Ctags (the BSD ctags that comes with OSX is bad)
